Sports Reporter Listed financial services giant, FBC Holdings has disbursed $35 000 to the Warriors who recently returned from Cameroon where they participated at the 2022 Africa Cup of Nations finals. The company pledged to give each player $1000 for every win at the continental showcase and following Zimbabweâ€™s 2-1 win over Guinea on Tuesday. Only three players, Takudzwa Chimwemwe, Martin Mapisa and Gerald Takwara were available to receive their cash. Coach Norman Mapeza and team manager Wellington Mpandare were at hand to receive their share. FBC Holdings had pledged to give the players houses, if they were to win the cup, but they were knocked out of the competition following defeats to Senegal and Malawi. The company pledged to support the Warriors in future.